args:
As the prince and his allies struggle to stop a
wave of fiends and villagers afflicted with a
condition known as ＂wroth,＂ people calling
themselves an angel and his apostles appear.
They are able to suppress the wroth affliction,
so the prince and his friends join in the fight.
Leave this to... ...get to safe...\n...ust go!
Roger tha... Everyone, with...\n...and don't look back!
What?! Y—p out of it! What's g—to ya?!
This man's wits have abandoned him.\nEveryone, behind me!
The entire region is steeped in malevolent\nmana... Whatever is happening here?
Nrgh?! Oh man, I don't feel so hot...
Well, we can't have that, now can we?\nHere's a little something to perk you up.
C-C-C-COOOLD! What's the big idea, pal?!
Easy, big fella. Won't take a minute.

Grant me now the glory of thy name, that
I may offer thy salvation unto the people
of the world and grant succor unto the
consecrated. ...Aaaand boom. Done.
The mana here has been purified!\nThat evil aura is gone, and all the\nvillagers sleep peacefully once more!

Holy water, custom-made. Works like a
charm to purify those tainted by miasma.
My friends are currently spraying the area
down with it.
My portion, at least, is complete.
Quick as ever, Ramiel.\nHow's your holy water stock?
Depleted. We shall need to replenish\nour stores post-haste.
Pinon here, reporting for duty and\nready to begin purification at once!
Glad to see ya in one piece, boss!
Barely, but I'll take it. Er, but who are\nthese folks here?
Sorry, friend, but we gotta finish clearing\nout this miasma before moving on to\npleasantries. C'mon, Pinon. Let's hoof it.

Blessed Goddess, grant us the glory of thy
name. May thy tears wash over the people
and show them the way, and grant mercy
to all who walk upon consecrated land.

May their feet be shod in scripture and
their hands in thy holy teachings gloved.
Grant peace and respite unto all who pass
now from shadow into the purity of light.
Grant thy vast and holy radiance, \nthat all darkness here be banished!
Sooo, can we get back to the whole\n＂who the hell are you people＂ part?
I'm Nevin—or Papa Bear, if you prefer.\nThe little lady with wings sprouting from\nher noggin there is Pinon.
And the bespectacled dragon with the look\nof a base villain is our dear Ramiel.
Ramiel? He of the Five Archangels?!
It seems my fame extends as far\nas the southern Church.
Then it IS you! And if you are indeed the\nArchangel Ramiel, then the pair with you\nmust be apostles.
W-well, I wouldn't say... I mean...

Easy there, Pinon. No sense trying to lie
our way out of it now. 'Sides, we woulda
ended up telling 'em once we asked for
their help anyway.
You have always been far too lax\nwith this manner of thing, Nevin.
I know this is gonna shock everybody,\nbut I'm confused. Somebody wanna break\ndown this ＂archangel and apostle＂ stuff?

The Five Archangels hear the voice of the
Goddess and serve as Her mouthpieces.
This makes them unique, and grants them
a special place among dragons.

Writings tell of the archangels scouting out
individuals of uncommon power known as
apostles and leading them into the field
on missions of great import.
So they're buddies of yours, basically.
It may seem a technical distinction,\nbut these people hail from the\nIlian Church of Grams.

Simply put, it's the branch of the faith
practiced in North Grastaea. It differs
from yours here in both organizational
structure and scriptural interpretation.
Though I might take exception at the label\n＂Ilian Church of Grams.＂
We are the original faith. As the newer\nsect, yours should be more properly\ncalled the Ilian Church of Alberia.
Hey now, no call to get snippy—we can\ndebate scripture another time. What's it\nmatter who came first at this point?

You say as much, yet divisions between
north and south are a sensitive matter
indeed. The fact you've come here
nevertheless can only mean...

Yer onto somethin' big. And if I was a
bettin' man—which I totally am, by the
way—I'd say it's got to do with all them
villagers goin' rabid.

Oh, I DO enjoy working with people who
are quick on the uptake! Good to see the
traitorous prince's merry band lives up to
its most impressive reputation.
Eh, we've done our homework—as we\nwould for any prospective ally.
We are here on classified orders\nfrom the Church.

All I can say further is that successful
completion of those orders will end the
phenomenon you just witnessed—a state
known as being ＂wroth,＂ by the way.
Yeah, that don't really tell us much.
If your intention is to cooperate with us,\nsurely you can afford to share a bit more?

Yeah, that's tricky. See, we're not trying
to keep mum out of spite, but... Well, I
guess it's one more thing you'll have to
accept on faith.
In that case, we'll do what we can.
Ya sure, boss? I've smelled wharf markets\nless fishy than what these folks are sellin'.
I get that, Ranzal, but we can't ignore it\nif the local fiends and villagers are losing\ntheir senses and going wroth.
And though we've only spoken briefly,\nI don't get the impression these people\nwish us any harm.
Ha! You're even softer than the rumors say.
I will thank you to temper your words\ntoward His Highness. But given that,\nwhat would you have us do?
First, we seek the use of your Halidom\nas our base of operations.
Second, we would install a statue of the\nGoddess within the castle premises.
To stave off the wroth! Statues of Ilia\nexude a holy mana that purifies the\nsurrounding area of miasma.
Remember the holy water I used before?\nIt was made by infusing spring water with\nmana from the ore used in those statues.
For each type of mana, there is a form or\nenvironment best suited to its cultivation.
Our search for the ideal form in which to\nproduce mana that dispels miasma led us\nto statues of the Goddess.

Seems pretty arbitrary that miasma-killing
mana would just happen to favor statues
of Ilia, but I guess folks with faith get to
stumble into salvation sometimes.
Pray do not undermine our work so, Nevin.\nIt is an affront to the Goddess.
You may be straight as a board, Pinon,\nbut I trust Ilia has a sense of humor.
Perhaps, but her believers may be less\nforgiving if they catch wind of your\ncasual blasphemy.
Grim thought, that—especially since I'm\ntoo old to relish the thought of trouble.\nWhat say we keep this between us?
Well, Prince? What do you say? Wanna\nwork with us and solve this business of\nfolks going wroth and losing it?
Of course. Sounds like we should start with\nerecting a statue of Ilia in the Halidom.
Don't worry, I'll make sure she's hot.
*sigh* In any case, I suspect our alliance\nwill be brief, yet pray it will be fruitful.
